  "text": "The parameters of the APH(N − Proof. The theorem is a consequence of Cumani's seminal result (Theorem 2.2.1) [CITATION_1] . Since any APH(N ) can be represented in canonical form, there is an APH(N ) with the given moments if and only if there is an APH(N − 1)-EXP structure with the given constraints.",
